    <thetext>Test execution should be based on the configurations/services that are available on the test target. For example if the puppet configuration specifies Trac 0.12 and Trac 1.0 tests should dynamically discovery these instances and run the test suite against those configurations.

I would propose a simple JSon file that is created as part of the provisioning and used to initialize test fixtures.

Here is an example for Trac (http://localhost:2080/cgi-bin/services):

[
{ 
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;trac&quot;, 
&quot;url&quot;: &quot;/trac-cert/&quot;, 
&quot;version&quot;: &quot;1.0&quot;, 
&quot;info&quot;: &quot;CertAuth&quot; 
}
{ 
&quot;type&quot;: &quot;trac&quot;, 
&quot;url&quot;: &quot;/trac-trunk/&quot;, 
&quot;version&quot;: &quot;trunk&quot;, 
&quot;info&quot;: &quot;&quot; 
}
]</thetext>
